It's measuring for jump forgivance, otherwise dubbed "coyote time". It allows the player to input a jump when the character technically isnt touching the floor, although to the human eye it's perceived otherwise. I assume this countdown is simply a float that resets to 0.15 whenever is_on_floor() is true, and is subtracted by frame time (delta) until it reaches zero when the method returns a false. It's a pretty surefire way of doing it. I would probably do the same for the sake of simplicity.
Alternatively, all of this can be disregarded; Coyote time is the time spent hanging out with a coyote.
